  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ending violence against children: child protection and reintegration of children in conflict with the law in Kinshasa and Goma.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1) With the helpline, children will be provided with advice from trained \\\&quot;listeners\\\&quot; (social workers, members of child parliament). State agents (DIVAS, police, CT, etc.) will have their capacities strengthened through training and provision of equipments. 
(2) Prevention and sensitisation activities will be undertaken through multi-media campaigns. A participative research activity will be undertaken through multimedia campaigns.;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Despite the fact that the LCP is considered as a model for its comprehensivenessm the Congolese population is barely aware of its content, and children have no one to go to when they are victims of violence. DIVAS, the ministry in charge of CP, does not have the capacities nor the resources for its implementation.;</narrative>
  </description>
